<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson & Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada & Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson & Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda & Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766434>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Habitus (upper, lateral view; lower, dorsal view) of species of the Colocasiomyia cristata subgroup.A, C. ecornuta sp. nov. ♂; B, C. grandis sp. nov. ♂; C, C. vieti sp. nov. ♂; D, C. cristata de Meijere ♂; E, C. sulawesiana Okada & Yafuso ♂; F, C. kinabaluana sp. nov. ♂; G, C. kotana sp. nov. ♂; and H, C. matthewsi sp. nov. ♂. Scale bars: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766434/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766464>
    dc:description "FIGURE 29. Colocasiomyia leucocasiae Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Bogor, West Java, Indonesia). A, Wing anterodistal portion; B, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); D, periphallic organs (lateral view); E, phallic organs (lateral view); F, ditto (ventral view); G, female terminalia (lateral view); H, puparium (ventral habitus); I, caudal-most portion of puparium (ventral view); J, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); K, mouth hook; L, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–G and L, 1.0 mm in H." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766464/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766414>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Character 12 of costal setae on the wing (anterodistal portion) of Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (A), C. colocasiae (Duda) (B) and C. cristata de Meijere (C). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766414/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766460>
    dc:description "FIGURE 27. Colocasiomyia diconica (Toda & Okada) (♂ and ♀ from Taykoa, Bangkok, Thailand).A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766460/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766432>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Geographical distributions of all species of the Colocasiomyia cristata group." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766432/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766466>
    dc:description "FIGURE 30. Flower-visiting and -breeding habits of Colocasiomyia cristata de Meijere on inflorescences/infructescences of Alocasia alba Schott at the Bogor Botanical Garden in West Java.A, Adult flies gathering in the pistillate (lower female-flowers) region of spadix at Stage II; B, adult flies crawling up from the pistillate to the staminate (upper male-flowers) region of spadix at Stage III and dusted with pollen grains; C, eggs laid between pistils; D, a developing infructescence at Stage V, with a hole at the top of spathal wall (indicated with arrowhead)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766466/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766468>
    dc:description "FIGURE 31. Distribution of Colocasiomyia pre-imagoes (eggs, larvae and puparia) over the spadix of inflorescence/ infructescence of host plant. A, Colocasiomyia cristata de Meijere on Alocasia alba Schott at the Bogor Botanical Garden in West Java; B, C. sulawesiana Okada & Yafuso on Alocasia macrorrhizos (L.) G. Don in South Sulawesi; C, C. leucocasiae Toda, sp. nov. on Leucocasia gigantea (Blume) Schott at the Bogor Botanical Garden in West Java; D, C. sabahana Toda, sp. nov. on Alocasia scabriuscula N.E.Br. at the headquarters area of Kinabalu Park in Sabah." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766468/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766470>
    dc:description "FIGURE 32. Evolution of host-plant selection in the Colocasiomyia cristata species group, estimated parsimoniously by ACCTRAN and DELTRAN using PAUP* v4.0a168.ACCTRAN and DELTRAN estimated the same changes and/or acquirement of host-plant genera, which are shown on corresponding branches." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766470/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766448>
    dc:description "FIGURE 21. Colocasiomyia kinabaluana Toda & Takano, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia). A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view); G, oviscapt (lateral view); H, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); I, puparium (ventral habitus; inset: caudal-most portion); J, mouth hook; K, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–G and K, 1.0 mm in I." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766448/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766450>
    dc:description "FIGURE 22. Colocasiomyia kotana Toda & Takano, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia). A, Male abdominal sternites (ventral view); B, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); C, periphallic organs (lateral view); D, phallic organs (lateral view); E, ditto (ventral view); F, female terminalia (lateral view); G, anterior spiracles of puparium (dorsal view); H, puparium (ventral habitus; inset: caudal-most portion); I, mouth hook; J, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A–F and J, 1.0 mm in H." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5766450/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

